      "blocks": {
        "heading_research": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Hydration Backed by Real Research",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_research": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Electrolytes play a critical role in maintaining hydration during physically demanding conditions. In a field study of wildland firefighters performing extended high-intensity work, researchers found that electrolyte solutions allowed workers to maintain hydration while consuming significantly less total water compared with water alone.</p><p><em>Hydration isn't just about drinking more water. It's about absorbing it effectively.</em></p>"
          }
        },
